{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"clerkish-undefeated-cicada","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## What\n\nMove the strict eval-spec discipline check — currently an inline Python step in the\n`Prompt Eval` GitHub Actions workflow (`.github/workflows/prompt-eval.yml`) — into a\nunit test that runs in the default pytest suite, and remove the now-redundant inline step.\n\nThe check: for every packaged `src/rebar/llm/eval_specs/*.eval.yaml`, `validate_eval_spec(spec)`\nmust be clean, and every dataset-bearing spec must additionally pass `validate_eval_spec(spec,\nstrict=True)` (registered scorers + balanced dataset + non-empty gold_set).\n\n## Why (necessity)\n\nThe `Verified` Gerrit vote is assembled by `gerrit-verify.yaml`, whose `vote` job aggregates\n`build-and-test`, `optionality`, `golden-path`, and `verify-identity`. It does NOT reference\n`prompt-eval.yml`, so the strict validation does not gate `Verified` and does not block a Gerrit\nsubmit. Concrete evidence: three advisory plan-review specs (asserted-capability, decomp-shape,\nnecessity) each shipped a `dataset` with no `gold_set` and MERGED green (Verified +1) while the\nstandalone Prompt Eval workflow was red — the defect only reddened a non-gating workflow after\nthe fact (fixed in bug d37b). The strict glob-validation lives ONLY in the inline CI script; no\nunit test covers it (the existing `test_new_eval_specs.py` enumerates a hardcoded 3-spec tuple,\nso new specs are never checked). The default suite (`pytest -m \"not integration and not external\"`)\nruns in both `_build-and-test.yml` callers, so a test there blocks `Verified` pre-merge.\n\n## Scope\n\n- Add a glob-based test to `tests/unit/test_eval_scorers.py` (which already globs all packaged\n  specs and runs in the default suite) mirroring the inline CI logic exactly.\n- Remove the redundant \"Validate every packaged eval spec\" inline step from `prompt-eval.yml`\n  (the offline job still runs `test_eval_scorers.py`); update the header comment for accuracy.\n- No production/library code changes.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] A unit test in `tests/unit/test_eval_scorers.py` globs every packaged eval spec and asserts\n      `validate_eval_spec(spec)` is clean, plus `validate_eval_spec(spec, strict=True)` clean for\n      every dataset-bearing spec; it is collected by the default (non-integration, non-external) suite.\n- [ ] The redundant inline validation step is removed from `.github/workflows/prompt-eval.yml`.\n- [ ] The new test fails if any dataset-bearing packaged spec lacks a gold_set (verified by a\n      local red→green check), and passes on current `main`.\n- [ ] `make lint` and the eval test suite pass; the `Prompt Eval` and `Verified` gates are green.","id":"1a5f-6f5d-6673-40b4","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Gate eval-spec strict validation via a unit test (not only the standalone Prompt Eval workflow)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784483061549013001,"uuid":"c85e3a2f-8eba-42f9-a208-f9cd9820d159"}